Suppose you have 1 million records.like amazon which handles a massive
no.of products
how would you handle pagination?


Why NOT Offset pagination?
Offset pagination works by skipping a certain number of rows

SELECT * FROM products ORDER BY id LIMIT 10 OFFSET 1000;

Why Keyset pagination?
--Keyset pagination retrieves records based on a specific key(usually a unique,indexed column like
id or timestamp). This makes it faster, especially for large datasets.

First API call:
/products?key=O&pageSize=10

SELECT * from products WHERE id > 0 ORDER BY id LIMIT 10

it returns first 10 records

amazon applies infinite pagescrolling.















